# Entity: Example

## Description
A placeholder entity demonstrating the standard CRUD pattern. Replace this with your domain-specific entities.

## Fields

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| id | UUID | Yes | Primary key |
| title | String | Yes | Item title |
| description | String | No | Item description |
| status | Enum | Yes | Status: DRAFT, PUBLISHED, ARCHIVED |
| createdBy | UUID | Yes | FK to User who created this item |
| createdAt | DateTime | Yes | Creation timestamp |
| updatedAt | DateTime | Yes | Last update timestamp |

## Relationships

- **belongs to** [User](user.md) - the user who created the item

## Validation Rules

- `title`: 1-255 characters, required
- `description`: max 2000 characters
- `status`: defaults to DRAFT

## Business Logic

- Only the creator or admins can update/delete an item
- Published items are visible to all authenticated users
- Draft items are only visible to the creator
- Archived items are soft-deleted (hidden from lists but data preserved)

## Database

- **Table name**: `examples`
- **Indexes**: index on `created_by`, index on `status`
- **Migration**: `V1__init.sql`

